<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://marvel-universe.com/min/poem.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=deldrach>Deldrach</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/21/03 3:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2026.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re:</span><hr size=1> I have to assume he is talking about FFXI because it is due for release on the 28th. Yes it is like EQ in that it is an MMORPG with dedicated servers. I was in the PS2 Beta and liked quite a bit of the stuff they did with it, but it wasn't necessarily my cup of tea. A bunch of my RL friends are jumping into this though so I might just buy the PC version and give it another shot even though I am getting free PS2 Hard drive loaded with FFFXI (( though that won't be released until March, bleh... )).<br>
<br>
FYI this game is very very very group dependent, and don't expect to be able to solo past about level 20. There is one job (job=class by the way) in the game that can solo effectively and that is the beastmaster. Grouping however is pretty easy as there is a nice &quot;Form Party&quot; menu that you use when LFG. You have your raids as well, though in FFXI they are called &quot;alliances&quot; and allow for a maximum of 3 parties of 6 players.<br>
<br>
Any race/job combination is possible, and if you don't like a job that you pick you can always change to a different one, there is no need to start a new character. Theoretically, if given enough time, you could level every single job up to maximum. However, many of the jobs must be unlocked through different quests, and you only start out with the basic jobs available, such as Warrior, Black Mage, White Mage, etc. You are allowed a primary job, and in addition once you reach level 18 and complete the appropriate quest, a support job as well, which can be a maximum of 1/2 the level of your current main job. However, you don't gain experience for your support job, so you essentially have to switch back and forth, leveling up two jobs to get the most out of your support job. For example let's say you level up a black mage to 18, finish the support job quest, and then change class to white mage and level it up to 10. When you switch back to Black mage you would be a 18BM/9WM. If you switched back to white mage as a primary job, you would be a 10WM/5BM.<br>
<br>
Personally I started out as a warrior, and unlocked Dark Knight and Samarai, and got that combo going and it pretty much owned. The Black mage/white mage combo is pretty powerful, but so many people are playing mages that it was nice to try something different. Also expect to see a lot of Tarutarus running around.<br>
<br>
Yes, I am talking about these little bastards here...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.gaminggroundzero.com/images/ffxi/Tarutaru.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
