<br>
I have a few questions about FFXI that have not been addressed by any of the media I've seen regarding the game.  For starters, to what extent does this game resonate with its nominal series?  From the looks of it, it bears more of a likeness to the first titles, and to some extent FFIX and FFT.  At a glance, it appears to have been modeled on the mainstream MMORPG fantasy genre.  The return of the job class system and its potential for customization is a staple of the series, but the similarities end there, based on what I have gleaned from demo footage and screenshots.  Granted, that's hardly conclusive.<br>
<br>
One of the hallmarks of the Final Fantasy series is the roundabout way of transmitting common themes that establish a vague sense of continuity.  The system of spells, and the recurring enemies that individualize the series.  That's one of the principle draws for me, anyway.<br>
<br>
So, twenty questions:  <br>
<br>
Are there any familiar items or weapons?  Are there degrees of spells (e.g. Fire, Fira, Firaga)?  Is it possible to cast summon spells (e.g. Bahamut, Shiva, Ifirit)?  How many jobs are there really, as I have seen only a few mentioned on the official website?  Can you learn special abilities from equipment, or is it level-based?  Is the combat interface point and click or turn-based in Final Fantasy fashion?  How difficult is it to advance in level compared to the langorous crawl of EQ?  How expensive are these World Passes required to play on the same server as a friend?  Are chocobos costly, and can anyone ride them?<br>
<br>
More like ten questions, actually.  If you could disclose on some of the mechanics, I'd be much obliged.  For a game to which I have been looking forward for some time, I am not very knowledgeable of it.  Truthfully, I have my doubts.  The concept of a Final Fantasy MMORPG is almost too brilliant to be credible or viable. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.projectbag.com/cowboy_bebop/thumbnails/andy08_t.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-large;"> + </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.projectbag.com/cowboy_bebop/thumbnails/andy02_t.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-large;"> = </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://ic.pricegrabber.com/muze_images/Video/Covers/54/102754_89x160.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=targok>Targok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/21/03 8:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2026.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: FFXI</span><hr size=1> I plan on buying this since I'll have a PC capable of running it come Sun.<br>
