<br>
When you both install FFXI and log in and create a character, you don't get the chance to choose which server you will be on, and there is a good chance it will place each of your characters on different servers. However, what you can do is create a character, get a little bit of Gil, and buy something called a World Pass, which will initially not be very expensive at all. What this does is you can use this and it will give you a code that you then give to your husband so that he can put it in and get a character on your server. World passes will have 5 uses, so you can then use it 4 more times to allow other friends to put in a code and move their character to your server as well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maushi>Maushi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/27/03 10:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2026.topic&index=15>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Final Fantasy XI</span><hr size=1> Deldrach,<br>
